# BSP Learnings

A BSP is the software layer that allows an OS to run on specific hardware.

Without BSP:

Linux/QNX cannot talk to hardware
CPU cannot initialize peripherals
Drivers cannot access registers
Kernel cannot boot correctly


A BSP usually contains:

Component	Purpose
Bootloader	Initializes hardware and loads OS
Device Tree	Describes hardware to kernel
Kernel Config	Enables required drivers
Drivers	UART, SPI, I2C, CAN, Ethernet
Pinmux Config	Configures pin functionality
Clock Setup	Enables clocks
Memory Init	DDR initialization
Build System	Yocto/Buildroot
Flashing Scripts	Programs image to board
Debug Tools	UART/JTAG support



